The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Saturday, July 24, 2004 				 Aniston ready to get Derailed
																								Los Angeles, July 23 (Reuters): Jennifer Aniston is about to get Derailed.																								The former Friends star will join British actor Clive Owen (King Arthur) in the Miramax thriller based on James Siegels best-selling novel about a married advertising executive whose life takes an unpredictable turn when he misses his train to work.																								Production is scheduled to begin in autumn in London and Chicago. The film will mark Swedish filmmaker Mikael Hafstroms English-language directorial debut.
